76561198054346622,Recommended,279140,15535865,"Posted: 25 April, 2015",all,MrLiability,"When I first got this game, I kicked myself. It seemed a monumental struggle of micro-management and annoying AI diplomacy. The tutorial itself was an off-putting 40 minutes long and it skipped some pretty important information.After 4 hours of hard slog, I began to understand the game. After 6 hours, I'm actually starting to enjoy myself. This isn't an intuitive casual game. It takes a looooooong time to learn and a loooooonger time to play. The gameplay itself is very rewarding however, especially for Civilization fans who are upset by the recent dumbing-down of the series.Graphics aren't great. Icon based mainly, but they are sufficient for the job. Sound is little better, but the music nice and imperial. Chances are you'll be killing the volume and putting on your own favorite tracks pretty quickly though.I recommend this game for those looking for an immersive grand-strategy game. The learning curve is steep, but it is worth it."
