,Recommended,279140,15929214,"Posted: 21 May, 2015",all,Ponder,"This game is a massive change from World War IINo longer do you worry about building up cities to produce more and more with greater IPUs, instead your cities perpetually produce at the same rates, and you manage resource allocation and the stress of limited trading capacities.Research is approached very differently, with only one topic at a time being researched. You can expand research facilities to make the research go ""faster,"" but the system is still quite different.Save for a similar map being ruled by different countries (I mean, instead of Abyssinia you must worry about the Dervish State, and now instead of Austria, Hungary, and etc., you have the Habsburg empire swallowing Serbia. Forget about Poland.)Although the mechanics are entirely different from previous Muzzy Lane games, the experience is not by any means a bad one. The new challenge of using different, more archaic technology and units, the trench warfare tactics, and new powerful entities provide a unique experience in gaming.7/10"
