76561197990970000,Recommended,279140,16830261,"Posted: 1 July, 2015",all,nortdakotahitman,"Making History: The Great Waris one of the best turn based strategy games out there. The game is easy to get into, but slightly harder to learn. I quickly figured out how the game works after a 40 hour long campaign with Japan. The game does not give you a great tutorial, but it does help you with the very basic stuff.The strategy regarding theeconomyin this game is the hardest to master. You could have the greatest military strength in the world, but your tanks and ships may not have enough fuel to fight. Taking control of your country's resources is the key to winning the game. Without metal or coal, your nation will not be able to build anything. Invading a country and taking it over is a great way to boost your resource stockpiles for a little bit.The strategy regarding theground combatis a bit too easy in my opinion, but once the world hates you it does get harder. If you keep large amounts soldiers and tanks on the border, you will not have much troubled defending. I find armies of at least 30 divisions can hold any line. It is only later in the game that you have to worry about being outnumbered and outgunned by large enemy armies.The strategy regarding thenaval combatis what can make or break a nation. A nation without a navy is a nation that can be attacked from every direction. I would say that having the best navy is the most important thing in the game other than the economy. You will not be able to expand far and secure and land without a navy to make an opening for your troop ships. I failed to have a navy during my first campaign and that really caused my downfall. That and those filthy immigrants.The tech tree is very basic and easy to understand. I can say much on it because of how easy it is to research.Pros-Detailed units.A solution to every problem can be found.A grand strategy game that requires thinking.Not impossible for small countries.Devs put out updates like Tyler Perry puts out movies, except the quality is much better.Your people will rebel against you if you are not careful.Cons-The game gets fairly slow towards the 100th turn.Too many pop-ups for some people.Research is a bit too basic.Tutorial does not go in-depth.Cannot commit genocide, or have a plan for assimilating foreigners.I would rate this game a9.25/10"
